Plate Glass]]\n|align=center|7\n|[[Willie Knapp]]\n|[[John Nixon (horseman)|John Nixon]]\n|[[Robert T. Davies]]\n|1:47.00\n|-\n|align=center|1912\n|[[Plate Glass (horse)|Plate Glass]]\n|align=center|6\n|E. Martin\n|C. Patterson\n|[[Robert T. Davies]]\n|1:48.40\n|-\n|}\n\n{{refbegin}}*In 1978, [[Hopeful Answer]] finished first but was disqualified and set back to second.{{refend}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Canadian flat horse races]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Graded stakes races in Canada]]\n[[Category:Turf races in Canada]]\n[[Category:Flat horse races for four-year-olds]]\n[[Category:Recurring events established in 1912]]\n[[Category:Woodbine Racetrack]]\n[[Category:Fort Erie Race Track]]\n[[Category:1912 establishments in Ontario]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox horseraces\n| surface       = Turf\n| class         = Grade II\n| horse race    = Connaught Cup Stakes\n| image         =\n| caption       =\n| location      = [[Woodbine Racetrack]]<br>[[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| inaugurated   = 1912\n| race type     = [[Thoroughbred]] - [[Flat racing]]\n| website       = {{URL|https://woodbine.com/}}\n| distance      = {{convert|7|furlong|mi}}\n| track         = Left-handed\n| qualification = Four-Year-Olds & Up\n| weight        = Allowances\n| purse         = $196,750 (2017)\n| bonuses       =\n}}\nThe '''Connaught Cup Stakes''' is a [[Thoroughbred horse race]] run annually at [[Woodbine Racetrack]] in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada. Run in late May, the [[Graded stakes race|Grade II]] race is open to horses aged four and older.  Raced over a distance of seven [[furlong]]s on [[Grass|turf]], it currently offers a purse of $196,750.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.equibase.com/static/chart/pdf/WO060317CAN8.pdf|title=Chart of the 2017 Connaught Cup Stakes|last=Equibase}}</ref>\n\nThe Connaught Cup was first run in 1912 on dirt at Toronto's [[Old Woodbine Race Course]]. As a result of [[World War I]], there was no race held in 1918 and 1919 and it was not run in 1930. The [[Great Depression]] saw much consolidation in the [[horse racing]] industry with track owners reducing the number of races run and the amount of the purses being offered. The Connaught Cup was suspended after the 1932 running and was not revived until 1952. In 1956 it was moved to the newly built Woodbine Racetrack where in 1958 it was converted to a turf race.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cthsont.com/Domains/www.cthsont.com/CMSFiles/Docs/2018_CTHS_TIPSchedule_HR.pdf |title=Woodbine Thoroughbred Stakes Results 2017 |publisher=Ontario Racing |date=2017-04-01 |accessdate=2018-12-17}}</ref>\n\nIt was run in two divisions in 1984.\n\nSince inception, the race has been contested at various distances:<br>\n'''On dirt:'''\n* {{frac|1|1|16}} miles : 1912 through 1955 at Old Woodbine Race Course, 1956-1957 at Woodbine Racecourse\n\n'''On turf:'''\n* 7 furlongs : beginning 2010 at Woodbine Racetrack\n* 1 mile :  1994 at [[Fort Erie Racetrack]]\n* {{frac|1|1|16}} miles : 1958-1963, 1980\u201393, 1995-2009 at Woodbine Racetrack\n* {{frac|1|1|8}} miles : 1964-1966, 1979 at Woodbine Racetrack, 1967-1978 at Fort Erie Racetrack\n\n==Records==\n'''Speed  record:''' (at present distance of 7 furlongs)\n* 1:19.40 - Tower of Texas (2017)\n\n'''Most wins:'''\n* 2 - [[Plate Glass (horse)|Plate Glass]] (1912, 1913)\n* 2 - [[King Maple]] (1955, 1956)\n* 2 - [[E. Day]] (1964, 1965)\n* 2 - [[James Bay (horse)|James Bay]] (1968, 1969)\n* 2 - [[Bridle Path (horse)|Bridle Path]] (1981, 1984)\n* 2 - [[Kiridashi (horse)|Kiridashi]] (1997, 1998)\n* 2 - [[Something Extra]] (2012, 2013)\n\n'''Most wins by an owner:'''\n* 5 - [[J. K. L. Ross]] (1916, 1920, 1922, 1924, 1927)\n* 5 - [[Stafford Farms]] (1975, 1976, 1978, 1979, 1980)\n\n'''Most wins by a [[jockey]]:'''\n* 8 - [[Robin Platts]] (1968, 1969, 1975, 1976, 1978, 1979, 1988, 1992)\n\n'''Most wins by a [[Horse trainer|trainer]]:'''\n* 5 - [[Gil Rowntree]] (1975, 1976, 1978, 1979, 1980)\n\n==Winners==\n{| c